Behind our designing process ✍️🎨 Bora launches tomorrow 🐬🐊🩵

Young 2021 me,

You would never believe this day. Yesterday, I stood in front of nearly 500 young women at the very school where I got my degree. The Women in Business Club invited me to be a guest speaker and share my journey. Was I terrified? 100%%%%. But also one of the most beautiful moments of my life.

“What if no one cares? What if they’re bored?” And after all…so many people came up to talk, messaged me afterward, showed up just to hear my story. The amount of love and kindness I felt was and still is so overwhelming in the best way possible, and honestly, I’m still processing it.

Knowing that I may have even in a tiny small way impacted the lives of these young women is so magical. It’s the kind of moment that I will never forget, reminding me that all my fear and vulnerability can lead to something incredible somehow.

 “oh my English is so bad,” “I don’t know how to talk or sell to girls from different cultural background as mine,” “I barely have any money to start” all those things you thought were holding you back? You didn’t let them stop you. You went ahead, grew, and started a beautiful journey 🩵

—Me
If only I could hug and thank that 20-year-old girl for not spending that $1,000 on anything else. She bet on her dream, and it was 100% worth it 💫✨

Trip take over with @baileyisabella - Maui, Hawaii 📍

“Here are a few of my favorite moments from my recent trip to Maui

Photo 1 - Beautiful trees we would find while taking our daily walks at the North Shore of the island

Photos 2 & 3 - Haleakala volcano 🌋 A must go! More than 10,000 ft height view from there - absolutely stunning (must be prepared for very low temperatures, mainly on sunset time)

Photos 4 & 5- More of our daily walks with the dogs at the North Shore beaches of the Island

Photo 6 - Insaneeee poke I would eat everyday at their supermarket FoodLand that honestly beats any restaurant poke I have eaten before - highly recommend 

Photos 7,8,9 & 10 - Content day for @ismeswim ! I was lucky enough to meet Maya, an amazing & beautiful local girl from Maui who took me to her favorite secret spot in the Island for pics! 

Photos 11, 12 & 13- Local shops in Makawao 😍 literally couldn’t resist to the many charming stores at this neighborhood! Bought this beautiful hand made tie dye dress, and a hat with a hole in the top 😂 (so I can naturally light up my hair roots while in the sun)

The last images are random moments that just felt (too) special to me 🌈🌺 Feeling so grateful for this trip and this opportunity of exploring around this amazing island!”

-Bella
